parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel tank overflow/fuel spillage issue can cause gasoline to spill onto the vehicle, ground, and operator, posing a fire hazard and environmental concern.
symptoms: Fuel spills or sprays out of the filler neck when the tank is filled
often after the pump clicks off; fuel spills onto the vehicle
and operator; fuel tank overflows every time it is filled.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inlet Check Valve Failure for Gas Tank
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the inlet check valve for the gas tank can cause fuel to overflow and spill when filling up, leading to a potential fire hazard, environmental damage, and personal injury.
symptoms: Fuel overflows and spills when filling up
fuel splashes out of the filler tube and onto the person
fuel spills out of the tank before the pump shuts off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The Death Wobble can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, potentially leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle shakes violently
often occurring at speeds between 45-60 mph.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Issues (Left Rear Brake Locks Wheel)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake issue can cause the vehicle to lose control, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The left rear brake locks the wheel
especially during emergency stops or on wet pavement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering column fracture can cause the vehicle to become difficult to control, potentially leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The fuel filler neck overflow can cause damage to the paint and plastic wheel guard, and potentially lead to a fire hazard.
symptoms: The fuel filler neck overflows when filling the fuel tank.
